lyrics:
[Verse]
In the silence, I reached for the sky
Silver dreams and golden schemes passed me by
Searching for serenity, longing for peace
In a world consumed by vanity, my soul found no release

[Chorus]
Oh, where did it all go wrong
Lost in the symphony, singing a broken song
These silver dreams and golden schemes, now shattered and torn
I retraced my steps, forlorn and reborn
